public VolumeStats(Long accountID,
                      Long actualIOPS,

        Contains statistical data for an individual volume.
        Parameters:
        accountID - [required] AccountID of the volume owner.
        actualIOPS - [required] Current actual IOPS to the volume in the last 500 milliseconds.
        asyncDelay - (optional) The length of time since the volume was last synced with the remote cluster.
        averageIOPSize - [required] Average size in bytes of recent I/O to the volume in the last 500 milliseconds.
        burstIOPSCredit - [required] The total number of IOP credits available to the user.
        clientQueueDepth - [required] The number of outstanding read and write operations to the cluster.
        desiredMetadataHosts - [required] The volume services being migrated to if the volume metadata is getting migrated between volume services.
        latencyUSec - [required] The observed latency time, in microseconds, to complete operations to a volume.
        metadataHosts - [required] The volume services on which the volume metadata resides.
        nonZeroBlocks - [required] The number of 4KiB blocks with data after the last garbage collection operation has completed.
        readBytes - [required] Total bytes read by clients.
        readLatencyUSec - [required] The average time, in microseconds, to complete read operations.
        readOps - [required] Total read operations.
        throttle - [required] A floating value between 0 and 1 that represents how much the system is throttling clients
        timestamp - [required] The current time in UTC.
        totalLatencyUSec - [required] The average time, in microseconds, to complete read and write operations to a volume.
        unalignedReads - [required] For 512e volumes, the number of read operations that were not on a 4k sector boundary.
        unalignedWrites - [required] For 512e volumes, the number of write operations that were not on a 4k sector boundary.
        volumeAccessGroups - [required] List of volume access group(s) to which a volume belongs.
        volumeID - [required] Volume ID of the volume.
        volumeSize - [required] Total provisioned capacity in bytes.
        volumeUtilization - [required] A floating value that describes how much the client is using the volume.
        writeBytes - [required] Total bytes written by clients.
        writeLatencyUSec - [required] The average time, in microseconds, to complete write operations.
        writeOps - [required] Total write operations occurring on the volume.
        zeroBlocks - [required] Total number of 4KiB blocks without data after the last round of garbage collection operation has completed.
        Since:
        7.0

      • getAsyncDelay

        public Optional<String> getAsyncDelay()
        The length of time since the volume was last synced with the remote cluster. If the volume is not paired, this is null.


        NOTE: A target volume in an active replication state always has an asyncDelay of 0 (zero). Target volumes are system-aware during replication and assume async delay is accurate at all times.

      • getAverageIOPSize

        public Long getAverageIOPSize()
        Average size in bytes of recent I/O to the volume in the last 500 milliseconds.

      • getBurstIOPSCredit

        public Long getBurstIOPSCredit()
        The total number of IOP credits available to the user. When users are not using up to the Max IOPS, credits are accrued.

      • getClientQueueDepth

        public Long getClientQueueDepth()
        The number of outstanding read and write operations to the cluster.

      • getDesiredMetadataHosts

        public MetadataHosts getDesiredMetadataHosts()
        The volume services being migrated to if the volume metadata is getting migrated between volume services. A "null" value means the volume is not migrating.

      • getLatencyUSec

        public Long getLatencyUSec()
        The observed latency time, in microseconds, to complete operations to a volume. A "0" (zero) value means there is no I/) to the volume.

      • getMetadataHosts

        public Long getUnalignedReads()
        For 512e volumes, the number of read operations that were not on a 4k sector boundary. High numbers of unalignedReads may indicate improper partition alignment.

      • getUnalignedWrites

        public Long getUnalignedWrites()

        Values: 0 = Client is not using the volume 1 = Client is using their max >1 = Client is using their burst
